race.comment: Liked that SUN GIFT (12) kept on coming fresh over the mile in a race that returned a good rating. She is going to be better up to this trip with the run under her belt and Willow gets another good draw to work with. That's a recipe. SUNTORA (3) spotted them a good start at Pakenham but was good enough to round them up and win going away. Rating there is good enough to land the hattrick here but Cranbourne is not Pakenham and tipping looping from near last is not the way to go about it. Wary of the talent and the form that she is in. HANAFUBUKI (9) also turns up in good form. Ready to peak third up off the right races. STOP THE ROCK (1) might improve sharply for the return where he was just getting warmed up. DICTIONARY (4) continues to race well and this is hardly different to what he has been around the mark in of late.
